      "body" : "Nice!\r\n\r\nFWIW, In my own programs, I usually add a \"--free\" command line option, which optionally cleans up on exit (slowing down exit), rather than the rapid exit(0).  Similarly, since freeing the block index and other numerous structures is a lot of pointless work at shutdown for 99.9% of users, I would suggest something similar for bitcoind.",
